Method 2 PCA with min max normalisation

norm_minmax <- function(x){
                           (x- min(x)) /(max(x)-min(x))
                          }
normalise <- as.data.frame(lapply(new_data, norm_minmax))

Method 3 Mean normalisation

#Mean Normalisation
mean_norm_minmax <- function(x){
                                (x- mean(x)) /(max(x)-min(x))
                               }

mean_normalise <- as.data.frame(lapply(new_data, mean_norm_minmax))
mds <- cmdscale(dist(t(mean_normalise)))
plot(mds, xlab="Coordinate 1", ylab="Coordinate 2", 
  type = "p",bty="n",pch=19, cex=4 ,col="pink")
text(mds, labels=rownames(mds) )
# Add a title to the plot
title("MDS of Mean normalisation")

Robust scaler

robust_scalar<- function(x){(x- median(x)) /(quantile(x,probs = .75)-quantile(x,probs = .25))}

robust_scalar <- as.data.frame(lapply(new_data, robust_scalar))
mds <- cmdscale(dist(t(robust_scalar)))
plot(mds, xlab="Coordinate 1", ylab="Coordinate 2", 
  type = "p",bty="n",pch=19, cex=4 ,col="lightblue")
text(mds, labels=rownames(mds) )
# Add a title to the plot
title("MDS of Robust scaler")
